TITLE: Incorrect `any` Type Usage - TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: These code snippets demonstrate incorrect usage of the `any` type in TypeScript, as flagged by the `no-explicit-any` rule. The rule aims to prevent the use of `any` as a type annotation, encouraging more specific type definitions or the `unknown` type.
SOURCE: https://github.com/typescript-eslint/typescript-eslint/blob/main/packages/eslint-plugin/docs/rules/no-explicit-any.mdx#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const age: any = 'seventeen';
```

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const ages: any[] = ['seventeen'];
```

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const ages: Array<any> = ['seventeen'];
```

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
function greet(): any {}
```

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
function greet(): any[] {}
```

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
function greet(): Array<any> {}
```

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
function greet(): Array<Array<any>> {}
```

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
function greet(param: Array<any>): string {}
```

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
function greet(param: Array<any>): Array<any> {}
```

