TITLE: Type Imports with Prefer Type Imports
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates the correct code when the 'prefer' option is set to 'type-imports'. It uses import type to import Foo and Bar. This enforces that all type-only imports are explicitly marked as type imports.
SOURCE: https://github.com/typescript-eslint/typescript-eslint/blob/main/packages/eslint-plugin/docs/rules/consistent-type-imports.mdx#_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
import type { Foo } from 'Foo';
import type Bar from 'Bar';
type T = Foo;
const x: Bar = 1;
```

