TITLE: Defining Rule Options with TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how to define and handle rule options using TypeScript's type system. It demonstrates creating a rule that accepts a `preferredCase` option, specifying the message IDs and options types, defining the schema for validation, and setting default option values.
SOURCE: https://github.com/typescript-eslint/typescript-eslint/blob/main/docs/developers/Custom_Rules.mdx#_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
import { ESLintUtils } from '@typescript-eslint/utils';

type MessageIds = 'lowercase' | 'uppercase';

type Options = [
  {
    preferredCase?: 'lower' | 'upper';
  },
];

// Type: RuleModule<MessageIds, Options, ...>
export const rule = createRule<Options, MessageIds>({
  // ...
});
```

