TITLE: Custom Lint Rule Example in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates a custom lint rule that detects when a `fetch()` call is sending data to an intake API using an old format (tuple) and suggests a code fix to migrate to a key-value object format.
SOURCE: https://github.com/typescript-eslint/typescript-eslint/blob/main/packages/website/blog/2024-09-30-typed-linting.md#_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { endpoints } from "~/api";

const rawData = ["key", "value"] as const;

await fetch(endpoints.intake, {
  data: JSON.stringify(rawData)
  //                   ~~~~~~~
  // Don't pass a tuple to endpoints.intake. Pass a key-value object instead.
  // eslint(@my-team/custom-rule)
  // ...
  method: "POST",
});
```

