TITLE: Incorrect Readonly Parameter Types Example (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates examples of incorrect usage where function parameters are not typed as readonly, allowing potential mutation of inputs.  Includes examples for arrays, tuples, objects, custom array types, custom function types and union types.  Highlights how the rule identifies mutable parameters.
