TITLE: Supporting Multi-Pass Fixes in RuleTester
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet illustrates how to provide an array of strings for the `output` property to specify the expected output after each fix pass in the `RuleTester`. It demonstrates the updated approach to test rules with multi-pass fixes in typescript-eslint v8.
SOURCE: https://github.com/typescript-eslint/typescript-eslint/blob/main/packages/website/blog/2024-07-31-announcing-typescript-eslint-v8.md#_snippet_16

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { RuleTester } from '@typescript-eslint/rule-tester';
import rule from '../src/rules/my-rule.ts';

const ruleTester = new RuleTester();

ruleTester.run('my-rule', rule, {
  valid: [
    /* ... */
  ],
  invalid: [
    {
      code: 'const a = 1;',
      // Remove the line with string form of `output`
      output: 'const b = 1;',
      // Add the line with array form of `output`
      output: ['const b = 1;', 'const c = 1;'],
      errors: [
        /* ... */
      ],
    },
  ],
});
```

