TITLE: Object Literal with Excess Properties after Removing Type Parameter TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This example shows the TypeScript error that occurs after removing the unnecessary type parameter from the `serialize` function. TypeScript raises an error because the object literal has an excess property that is not defined in the `SomeProperties` interface.
